Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with video streaming and network capacity estimation. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper discusses video quality and rate selection algorithms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a new approach to controlling the playback buffer. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch on security concerns related to video streaming. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper may discuss the challenges of streaming video over distributed networks.
